==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|la|lavatorium}}, from {{m|la|lavō|lavāre|to [[wash]]}} + {{m|la|-ium|pos=forming places related to an activity}}. As a place to pan gold, via {{der|en|es|lavadero}}.<ref>"[http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/106352 lavatory], ''n.''" in the ''Oxford English Dictionary'' (1902), Oxford: Oxford University Press.</ref> ''See also'' '''[[lave]]'''.

